{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"chip-rib-gong","description":"## Why\n\nThe migration deliberately runs the bespoke plan-review gate and the new workflow gate in\nparallel, validated by the B4 planned-trace parity harness, and B5 cuts the live gate over to\nthe workflow while keeping the bespoke path reachable behind a flag as a fallback. Once parity\nis EXHAUSTIVELY validated and the workflow gate has run as the sole live gate without regression,\nthe scaffolding should come down — both the parity harness (a migration-validation tool) and the\nbespoke `orchestrator.run_review` path (now dead weight). Convergence: only what earns its keep\nremains. Without this story the epic leaves two parallel gate implementations + a harness in the\ntree indefinitely.\n\n## What\n\nRetire the migration scaffolding once the workflow gate is proven:\n- Remove the B4 **parity harness** (`tests/unit/workflow/test_plan_review_parity.py`,\n  `_parity_corpus.py`, and the `TracingFakeRunner` scaffolding in `trace.py` if unused elsewhere).\n- Retire the **bespoke plan-review path**: `orchestrator.run_review` + the bespoke-only fan-out\n  (the `ThreadPoolExecutor` Pass-1 driver) + the B5 fallback flag, so the engine workflow is the\n  SOLE plan-review gate. Keep the SHARED machinery the workflow still uses (`pass1.run_pass1`,\n  `det_floor`, `registry`, `passes`, `sizing`, `attest`, `ProductionBatchRunner`).\n- Preserve forwarding shims / public API for anything still referenced (`review_plan` library/CLI/\n  MCP entrypoints keep working, now backed only by the workflow path).\n\n## Scope\n\n- This is the FINAL convergence step; it must come AFTER B5 (cutover) and after parity is\n  exhaustively validated (the corpus is comprehensive AND a soak period with the workflow as the\n  sole live gate showed no regression — record the evidence on this ticket before deleting).\n- Delete dead bespoke code + the harness; update tests/docs; ensure the close/claim gates keep\n  working through the workflow path with signatures intact.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Parity is recorded as exhaustively validated (comprehensive corpus + a documented soak with\n      the workflow as the sole live gate, no regression) BEFORE any deletion.\n- [ ] The B4 parity harness + its corpus + the unused tracing scaffolding are removed.\n- [ ] The bespoke `orchestrator.run_review` path + its `ThreadPoolExecutor` fan-out + the B5\n      fallback flag are removed; the engine workflow is the sole plan-review gate; `review_plan`\n      library/CLI/MCP entrypoints still work (forwarding shims preserved).\n- [ ] No orphaned references to the removed code; `make lint` + the full test suite pass.","id":"961b-a3ff-63e4-465f","parent_id":"72d5-79ec-9e2e-4a2b","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"B-RETIRE: retire the parity harness + the bespoke plan-review path once parity is exhaustively validated"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782449371588261001,"uuid":"4a52cdeb-4062-4ec7-9cb9-b9ae1e484eb2"}